{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"This was in an area called Wellawatta, a prime residential area in Colombo."},{"time":5000,"text":"We stood on the railroad tracks"},{"time":7000,"text":"that ran between my friend's house and the beach."},{"time":10000,"text":"The tracks are elevated about eight feet from the waterline normally,"},{"time":13000,"text":"but at that point the water had receded"},{"time":15000,"text":"to a level three or four feet below normal."},{"time":18000,"text":"I'd never seen the reef here before."},{"time":20000,"text":"There were fish caught in rock pools left behind by the receding water."},{"time":25000,"text":"Some children jumped down and ran to the rock pools with bags."},{"time":29000,"text":"They were trying to catch fish."},{"time":31000,"text":"No one realized that this was a very bad idea."},{"time":34000,"text":"The people on the tracks just continued to watch them."},{"time":37000,"text":"I turned around to check on my friend's house."},{"time":40000,"text":"Then someone on the tracks screamed."},{"time":42000,"text":"Before I could turn around, everyone on the tracks was screaming and running."}]},{"cues":[{"time":46000,"text":"The water had started coming back. It was foaming over the reef."},{"time":50000,"text":"The children managed to run back onto the tracks."},{"time":54000,"text":"No one was lost there. But the water continued to climb."},{"time":58000,"text":"In about two minutes, it had reached the level of the railroad tracks"},{"time":61000,"text":"and was coming over it. We had run about 100 meters by this time."},{"time":65000,"text":"It continued to rise."},{"time":67000,"text":"I saw an old man standing at his gate, knee-deep in water, refusing to move."},{"time":72000,"text":"He said he'd lived his whole life there by the beach,"},{"time":75000,"text":"and that he would rather die there than run."},{"time":78000,"text":"A boy broke away from his mother to run back into his house"},{"time":81000,"text":"to get his dog, who was apparently afraid."},{"time":84000,"text":"An old lady, crying, was carried out of her house and up the road by her son."},{"time":89000,"text":"The slum built on the railroad reservation"},{"time":92000,"text":"between the sea and the railroad tracks was completely swept away."},{"time":96000,"text":"Since this was a high-risk location, the police had warned the residents,"},{"time":99000,"text":"and no one was there when the water rose."},{"time":101000,"text":"But they had not had any time to evacuate any belongings."},{"time":105000,"text":"For hours afterwards, the sea was strewn with bits of wood for miles around --"},{"time":109000,"text":"all of this was from the houses in the slum."},{"time":112000,"text":"When the waters subsided, it was as if it had never existed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":118000,"text":"This may seem hard to believe --"},{"time":120000,"text":"unless you've been reading lots and lots of news reports --"},{"time":122000,"text":"but in many places, after the tsunami, villagers were still terrified."},{"time":126000,"text":"When what was a tranquil sea swallows up people, homes"},{"time":129000,"text":"and long-tail boats -- mercilessly, without warning --"},{"time":131000,"text":"and no one can tell you anything reliable about whether another one is coming,"},{"time":135000,"text":"I'm not sure you'd want to calm down either."},{"time":138000,"text":"One of the scariest things about the tsunami"},{"time":140000,"text":"that I've not seen mentioned is the complete lack of information."},{"time":144000,"text":"This may seem minor, but it is terrifying to hear rumor after rumor"},{"time":147000,"text":"after rumor that another tidal wave, bigger than the last,"},{"time":150000,"text":"will be coming at exactly 1 p.m., or perhaps tonight, or perhaps ..."},{"time":155000,"text":"You don't even know if it is safe to go back down to the water,"},{"time":158000,"text":"to catch a boat to the hospital."},{"time":160000,"text":"We think that Phi Phi hospital was destroyed."},{"time":162000,"text":"We think this boat is going to Phuket hospital,"},{"time":165000,"text":"but if it's too dangerous to land at its pier,"},{"time":167000,"text":"then perhaps it will go to Krabi instead, which is more protected."},{"time":171000,"text":"We don't think another wave is coming right away."}]},{"cues":[{"time":174000,"text":"At the Phi Phi Hill Resort,"},{"time":176000,"text":"I was tucked into the corner furthest away from the television,"},{"time":179000,"text":"but I strained to listen for information."},{"time":181000,"text":"They reported that there was an 8.5 magnitude earthquake in Sumatra,"},{"time":184000,"text":"which triggered the massive tsunami."},{"time":186000,"text":"Having this news was comforting in some small way"},{"time":188000,"text":"to understand what had just happened to us."},{"time":190000,"text":"However, the report focused on what had already occurred"},{"time":193000,"text":"and offered no information on what to expect now."},{"time":196000,"text":"In general, everything was merely hearsay and rumor,"},{"time":199000,"text":"and not a single person I spoke to for over 36 hours"},{"time":202000,"text":"knew anything with any certainty."},{"time":205000,"text":"Those were two accounts of the Asian tsunami from two Internet blogs"},{"time":211000,"text":"that essentially sprang up after it occurred."},{"time":214000,"text":"I'm now going to show you two video segments from the tsunami"},{"time":219000,"text":"that also were shown on blogs."},{"time":221000,"text":"I should warn you, they're pretty powerful."},{"time":223000,"text":"One from Thailand, and the second one from Phuket as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":227000,"text":"(Screaming)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":241000,"text":"Voice 1: It's coming in. It's coming again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":244000,"text":"Voice 2: It's coming again?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":246000,"text":"Voice 1: Yeah. It's coming again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":248000,"text":"Voice 2: Come get inside here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":252000,"text":"Voice 1: It's coming again. Voice 2: New wave?"},{"time":257000,"text":"Voice 1: It's coming again. New wave!"},{"time":262000,"text":"[Unclear]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":266000,"text":"(Screaming)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":287000,"text":"They called me out here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":303000,"text":"James Surowiecki: Phew. Those were both on this site: waveofdestruction.org."},{"time":309000,"text":"In the world of blogs, there's going to be before the tsunami and after the tsunami,"},{"time":313000,"text":"because one of the things that happened in the wake of the tsunami was that,"},{"time":317000,"text":"although initially -- that is, in that first day --"},{"time":319000,"text":"there was actually a kind of dearth of live reporting, there was a dearth of live video"},{"time":323000,"text":"and some people complained about this."},{"time":325000,"text":"They said, \"The blogsters let us down.\""},{"time":328000,"text":"What became very clear was that,"},{"time":330000,"text":"within a few days, the outpouring of information was immense,"},{"time":335000,"text":"and we got a complete and powerful picture of what had happened"},{"time":340000,"text":"in a way that we never had been able to get before."},{"time":343000,"text":"And what you had was a group of essentially unorganized, unconnected"},{"time":346000,"text":"writers, video bloggers, etc., who were able to come up with"},{"time":351000,"text":"a collective portrait of a disaster that gave us a much better sense"},{"time":355000,"text":"of what it was like to actually be there than the mainstream media could give us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":360000,"text":"And so in some ways the tsunami can be seen as a sort of seminal moment,"},{"time":364000,"text":"a moment in which the blogosphere came, to a certain degree, of age."},{"time":370000,"text":"Now, I'm going to move now from this kind of --"},{"time":372000,"text":"the sublime in the traditional sense of the word,"},{"time":374000,"text":"that is to say, awe-inspiring, terrifying -- to the somewhat more mundane."},{"time":379000,"text":"Because when we think about blogs,"},{"time":381000,"text":"I think for most of us who are concerned about them,"},{"time":384000,"text":"we're primarily concerned with things like politics, technology, etc."},{"time":389000,"text":"And I want to ask three questions in this talk,"},{"time":391000,"text":"in the 10 minutes that remain, about the blogosphere."},{"time":395000,"text":"The first one is, What does it tell us about our ideas,"},{"time":398000,"text":"about what motivates people to do things?"},{"time":400000,"text":"The second is, Do blogs genuinely have the possibility"},{"time":404000,"text":"of accessing a kind of collective intelligence"},{"time":408000,"text":"that has previously remained, for the most part, untapped?"},{"time":411000,"text":"And then the third part is, What are the potential problems,"},{"time":415000,"text":"or the dark side of blogs as we know them?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":419000,"text":"OK, the first question:"},{"time":421000,"text":"What do they tell us about why people do things?"},{"time":423000,"text":"One of the fascinating things about the blogosphere specifically,"},{"time":426000,"text":"and, of course, the Internet more generally --"},{"time":429000,"text":"and it's going to seem like a very obvious point,"},{"time":431000,"text":"but I think it is an important one to think about --"},{"time":433000,"text":"is that the people who are generating these enormous reams of content"},{"time":437000,"text":"every day, who are spending enormous amounts of time organizing,"},{"time":442000,"text":"linking, commenting on the substance of the Internet,"},{"time":445000,"text":"are doing so primarily for free."},{"time":448000,"text":"They are not getting paid for it in any way other than in the attention and,"},{"time":452000,"text":"to some extent, the reputational capital that they gain from doing a good job."},{"time":457000,"text":"And this is -- at least, to a traditional economist -- somewhat remarkable,"},{"time":462000,"text":"because the traditional account of economic man would say that,"},{"time":466000,"text":"basically, you do things for a concrete reward, primarily financial."},{"time":471000,"text":"But instead, what we're finding on the Internet --"},{"time":474000,"text":"and one of the great geniuses of it -- is that people have found a way"},{"time":478000,"text":"to work together without any money involved at all."},{"time":481000,"text":"They have come up with, in a sense, a different method for organizing activity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":486000,"text":"The Yale Law professor Yochai Benkler, in an essay called \"Coase's Penguin,\""},{"time":491000,"text":"talks about this open-source model, which we're familiar with from Linux,"},{"time":495000,"text":"as being potentially applicable in a whole host of situations."},{"time":498000,"text":"And, you know, if you think about this with the tsunami,"},{"time":500000,"text":"what you have is essentially a kind of an army of local journalists,"},{"time":504000,"text":"who are producing enormous amounts of material"},{"time":507000,"text":"for no reason other than to tell their stories."},{"time":509000,"text":"That's a very powerful idea, and it's a very powerful reality."},{"time":513000,"text":"And it's one that offers really interesting possibilities"},{"time":515000,"text":"for organizing a whole host of activities down the road."}]},{"cues":[{"time":521000,"text":"So, I think the first thing that the blogosphere tells us"},{"time":524000,"text":"is that we need to expand our idea of what counts as rational,"},{"time":527000,"text":"and we need to expand our simple equation of value equals money,"},{"time":531000,"text":"or, you have to pay for it to be good,"},{"time":533000,"text":"but that in fact you can end up with collectively really brilliant products"},{"time":536000,"text":"without any money at all changing hands."},{"time":539000,"text":"There are a few bloggers -- somewhere maybe around 20, now --"},{"time":542000,"text":"who do, in fact, make some kind of money, and a few"},{"time":545000,"text":"who are actually trying to make a full-time living out of it,"},{"time":548000,"text":"but the vast majority of them are doing it because they love it"},{"time":550000,"text":"or they love the attention, or whatever it is."},{"time":552000,"text":"So, Howard Rheingold has written a lot about this"},{"time":554000,"text":"and, I think, is writing about this more,"},{"time":556000,"text":"but this notion of voluntary cooperation"},{"time":559000,"text":"is an incredibly powerful one, and one worth thinking about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":562000,"text":"The second question is, What does the blogosphere actually do for us,"},{"time":567000,"text":"in terms of accessing collective intelligence?"},{"time":570000,"text":"You know, as Chris mentioned, I wrote a book called \"The Wisdom of Crowds.\""},{"time":573000,"text":"And the premise of \"The Wisdom of Crowds\" is that,"},{"time":576000,"text":"under the right conditions, groups can be remarkably intelligent."},{"time":580000,"text":"And they can actually often be smarter"},{"time":582000,"text":"than even the smartest person within them."},{"time":584000,"text":"The simplest example of this is if you ask a group of people"},{"time":587000,"text":"to do something like guess how many jellybeans are in a jar."},{"time":591000,"text":"If I had a jar of jellybeans"},{"time":593000,"text":"and I asked you all to guess how many jellybeans were in that jar,"},{"time":596000,"text":"your average guess would be remarkably good."},{"time":599000,"text":"It would be somewhere probably within three and five percent"},{"time":601000,"text":"of the number of beans in the jar,"},{"time":603000,"text":"and it would be better than 90 to 95 percent of you."},{"time":608000,"text":"There may be one or two of you who are brilliant jelly bean guessers,"},{"time":611000,"text":"but for the most part the group's guess"},{"time":614000,"text":"would be better than just about all of you."},{"time":616000,"text":"And what's fascinating is that you can see this phenomenon at work"},{"time":619000,"text":"in many more complicated situations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":622000,"text":"For instance, if you look at the odds on horses at a racetrack,"},{"time":625000,"text":"they predict almost perfectly how likely a horse is to win."},{"time":630000,"text":"In a sense, the group of betters at the racetrack"},{"time":633000,"text":"is forecasting the future, in probabilistic terms."},{"time":637000,"text":"You know, if you think about something like Google,"},{"time":639000,"text":"which essentially is relying on the collective intelligence of the Web"},{"time":643000,"text":"to seek out those sites that have the most valuable information --"},{"time":647000,"text":"we know that Google does an exceptionally good job of doing that,"},{"time":650000,"text":"and it does that because, collectively, this disorganized thing"},{"time":653000,"text":"we call the \"World Wide Web\" actually has a remarkable order,"},{"time":657000,"text":"or a remarkable intelligence in it."},{"time":660000,"text":"And this, I think, is one of the real promises of the blogosphere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":663000,"text":"Dan Gillmor -- whose book \"We the Media\""},{"time":665000,"text":"is included in the gift pack --"},{"time":667000,"text":"has talked about it as saying that, as a writer,"},{"time":670000,"text":"he's recognized that his readers know more than he does."},{"time":674000,"text":"And this is a very challenging idea. It's a very challenging idea"},{"time":677000,"text":"to mainstream media. It's a very challenging idea to anyone"},{"time":679000,"text":"who has invested an enormous amount of time and expertise,"},{"time":683000,"text":"and who has a lot of energy invested in the notion"},{"time":686000,"text":"that he or she knows better than everyone else."},{"time":691000,"text":"But what the blogosphere offers is the possibility"},{"time":694000,"text":"of getting at the kind of collective, distributive intelligence that is out there,"},{"time":699000,"text":"and that we know is available to us"},{"time":701000,"text":"if we can just figure out a way of accessing it."},{"time":705000,"text":"Each blog post, each blog commentary"},{"time":708000,"text":"may not, in and of itself, be exactly what we're looking for,"},{"time":712000,"text":"but collectively the judgment of those people posting, those people linking,"},{"time":717000,"text":"more often than not is going to give you a very interesting"},{"time":721000,"text":"and enormously valuable picture of what's going on."},{"time":724000,"text":"So, that's the positive side of it."},{"time":726000,"text":"That's the positive side of what is sometimes called"},{"time":728000,"text":"participatory journalism or citizen journalism, etc. --"},{"time":733000,"text":"that, in fact, we are giving people"},{"time":736000,"text":"who have never been able to talk before a voice,"},{"time":739000,"text":"and we're able to access information that has always been there"},{"time":742000,"text":"but has essentially gone untapped."}]},{"cues":[{"time":745000,"text":"But there is a dark side to this,"},{"time":747000,"text":"and that's what I want to spend the last part of my talk on."},{"time":750000,"text":"One of the things that happens if you spend a lot of time on the Internet,"},{"time":753000,"text":"and you spend a lot of time thinking about the Internet,"},{"time":755000,"text":"is that it is very easy to fall in love with the Internet."},{"time":759000,"text":"It is very easy to fall in love with the decentralized,"},{"time":762000,"text":"bottom-up structure of the Internet."},{"time":764000,"text":"It is very easy to think that networks are necessarily good things --"},{"time":769000,"text":"that being linked from one place to another,"},{"time":771000,"text":"that being tightly linked in a group, is a very good thing."},{"time":775000,"text":"And much of the time it is."},{"time":777000,"text":"But there's also a downside to this -- a kind of dark side, in fact --"},{"time":781000,"text":"and that is that the more tightly linked we've become to each other,"},{"time":785000,"text":"the harder it is for each of us to remain independent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":789000,"text":"One of the fundamental characteristics of a network is that,"},{"time":792000,"text":"once you are linked in the network,"},{"time":794000,"text":"the network starts to shape your views"},{"time":797000,"text":"and starts to shape your interactions with everybody else."},{"time":800000,"text":"That's one of the things that defines what a network is."},{"time":802000,"text":"A network is not just the product of its component parts."},{"time":806000,"text":"It is something more than that."},{"time":809000,"text":"It is, as Steven Johnson has talked about, an emergent phenomenon."},{"time":813000,"text":"Now, this has all these benefits:"},{"time":815000,"text":"it's very beneficial in terms of the efficiency of communicating information;"},{"time":818000,"text":"it gives you access to a whole host of people;"},{"time":821000,"text":"it allows people to coordinate their activities in very good ways."},{"time":824000,"text":"But the problem is that groups are only smart"},{"time":828000,"text":"when the people in them are as independent as possible."},{"time":832000,"text":"This is the paradox of the wisdom of crowds,"},{"time":835000,"text":"or the paradox of collective intelligence,"},{"time":837000,"text":"that what it requires is actually a form of independent thinking."},{"time":842000,"text":"And networks make it harder for people to do that,"},{"time":846000,"text":"because they drive attention to the things that the network values."}]},{"cues":[{"time":850000,"text":"So, one of the phenomena that's very clear in the blogosphere"},{"time":854000,"text":"is that once a meme, once an idea gets going,"},{"time":858000,"text":"it is very easy for people to just sort of pile on,"},{"time":861000,"text":"because other people have, say, a link."},{"time":864000,"text":"People have linked to it, and so other people in turn link to it, etc., etc."},{"time":867000,"text":"And that phenomenon"},{"time":870000,"text":"of piling on the existing links"},{"time":873000,"text":"is one that is characteristic of the blogosphere,"},{"time":876000,"text":"particularly of the political blogosphere,"},{"time":879000,"text":"and it is one that essentially throws off"},{"time":882000,"text":"this beautiful, decentralized, bottom-up intelligence"},{"time":885000,"text":"that blogs can manifest in the right conditions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":888000,"text":"The metaphor that I like to use is the metaphor of the circular mill."},{"time":892000,"text":"A lot of people talk about ants."},{"time":894000,"text":"You know, this is a conference inspired by nature."},{"time":896000,"text":"When we talk about bottom-up, decentralized phenomena,"},{"time":899000,"text":"the ant colony is the classic metaphor, because,"},{"time":903000,"text":"no individual ant knows what it's doing,"},{"time":905000,"text":"but collectively ants are able to reach incredibly intelligent decisions."},{"time":910793,"text":"They're able to reach food\nas efficiently as possible,"},{"time":913874,"text":"they're able to guide their traffic\nwith remarkable speed."},{"time":918000,"text":"So, the ant colony is a great model:"},{"time":920000,"text":"you have all these little parts that collectively add up to a great thing."},{"time":923000,"text":"But we know that occasionally ants go astray,"},{"time":927000,"text":"and what happens is that, if army ants are wandering around and they get lost,"},{"time":931000,"text":"they start to follow a simple rule --"},{"time":933000,"text":"just do what the ant in front of you does."},{"time":937000,"text":"And what happens is that the ants eventually end up in a circle."},{"time":941000,"text":"And there's this famous example of one that was 1,200 feet long"},{"time":945000,"text":"and lasted for two days, and the ants just kept marching around and around"},{"time":949000,"text":"in a circle until they died."},{"time":952000,"text":"And that, I think, is a sort of thing to watch out for."},{"time":955000,"text":"That's the thing we have to fear --"},{"time":957000,"text":"is that we're just going to keep marching around and around until we die."}]},{"cues":[{"time":961000,"text":"Now, I want to connect this back, though, to the tsunami,"},{"time":964000,"text":"because one of the great things about the tsunami --"},{"time":966000,"text":"in terms of the blogosphere's coverage,"},{"time":968000,"text":"not in terms of the tsunami itself --"},{"time":970000,"text":"is that it really did represent a genuine bottom-up phenomenon."},{"time":974000,"text":"You saw sites that had never existed before getting huge amounts of traffic."},{"time":977000,"text":"You saw people being able to offer up\ntheir independent points of view"},{"time":981000,"text":"in a way that they hadn't before."},{"time":983000,"text":"There, you really did see the intelligence of the Web manifest itself."},{"time":988000,"text":"So, that's the upside. The circular mill is the downside."},{"time":991000,"text":"And I think that the former is what we really need to strive for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":994000,"text":"Thank you very much. (Applause)"}]}]}